---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Projects - Ashton Andrepont">
	<section class="section">
		<h2>Technical Projects</h2>
		<p>
			A selection of technical projects demonstrating my expertise in software development, 
			algorithm implementation, and system design. These projects complement my research 
			work and showcase practical applications of computer science principles.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="project-item">
			<h3>Educational Resource Management System</h3>
			<p>
				Full-stack web application for managing educational resources in rural school districts. 
				Features include inventory tracking, automated ordering, and usage analytics with 
				machine learning-powered recommendations.
			</p>
			<p><strong>Technologies:</strong> React, Node.js, PostgreSQL, TensorFlow.js, Docker</p>
			<p><strong>Impact:</strong> Deployed in 3 Louisiana school districts, reducing administrative overhead by 40%</p>
			<div class="tags">
				<span class="tag">Full-Stack Development</span>
				<span class="tag">Machine Learning</span>
				<span class="tag">Education Technology</span>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="project-item">
			<h3>Quantum Circuit Simulator</h3>
			<p>
				Python implementation of a quantum circuit simulator with visualization capabilities. 
				Includes support for common quantum gates, measurement operations, and noise modeling 
				for NISQ device simulation.
			</p>
			<p><strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, NumPy, Matplotlib, Qiskit (for validation)</p>
			<p><strong>Features:</strong> Custom gate implementation, circuit optimization, noise simulation</p>
			<div class="tags">
				<span class="tag">Quantum Computing</span>
				<span class="tag">Python</span>
				<span class="tag">Scientific Computing</span>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="project-item">
			<h3>Adaptive Learning Algorithm Framework</h3>
			<p>
				Modular framework for implementing and testing adaptive learning algorithms. 
				Supports multiple learning models, A/B testing infrastructure, and real-time 
				performance analytics for educational applications.
			</p>
			<p><strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, scikit-learn, FastAPI, Redis, PostgreSQL</p>
			<p><strong>Validation:</strong> Tested with synthetic and real student data, 25% improvement in learning outcomes</p>
			<div class="tags">
				<span class="tag">Machine Learning</span>
				<span class="tag">Algorithm Design</span>
				<span class="tag">Educational Research</span>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="project-item">
			<h3>Rural Connectivity Assessment Tool</h3>
			<p>
				Web-based tool for assessing internet connectivity and technology infrastructure 
				in rural schools. Provides automated testing, reporting, and recommendations 
				for improving educational technology access.
			</p>
			<p><strong>Technologies:</strong> JavaScript, Python, Flask, SQLite, Chart.js</p>
			<p><strong>Usage:</strong> Deployed across 15+ rural Louisiana schools for infrastructure planning</p>
			<div class="tags">
				<span class="tag">Web Development</span>
				<span class="tag">Infrastructure Analysis</span>
				<span class="tag">Data Visualization</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Open Source Contributions</h2>
		<div class="project-item">
			<h3>Educational Data Standards Library</h3>
			<p>
				Python library for standardizing educational data formats across different 
				school information systems. Facilitates data interoperability and research collaboration.
			</p>
			<p><strong>Repository:</strong> <a href="#" style="color: var(--color-accent);">github.com/education-standards/python-lib</a></p>
			<div class="tags">
				<span class="tag">Open Source</span>
				<span class="tag">Data Standards</span>
				<span class="tag">Python Library</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Technical Skills</h2>
		<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">
			<div>
				<h3>Programming Languages</h3>
				<p>Python, JavaScript/TypeScript, C++, Java, R, SQL</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h3>Machine Learning</h3>
				<p>TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn, pandas, NumPy</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h3>Web Development</h3>
				<p>React, Node.js, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Docker</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h3>Quantum Computing</h3>
				<p>Qiskit, Cirq, quantum algorithm design</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
